-- Philippine Equity Movers: Marcventures, PLDT, Rizal Commercial
-- B y   N o r m a n   P .   A q u i n o
-- 2012-05-08T08:27:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-08/manila-electric-rizal-commercial-philippine-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in  Philippine (PASHR)  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in  Manila .  The  Philippine Stock Exchange Index (PCOMP)  rose 0.2 percent to
5,242.06.  Marcventures Holdings Inc. (MARC)   advanced 6.9 percent
to 3.43 pesos, the most since April 17 and snapping a three-day,
14 percent slide. The company said its mining unit has started
shipping nickel ore and that it will start a “major” drilling
and exploration program this year.  Philippine Long Distance Telephone Co. (TEL)   fell 0.6
percent to 2,536 pesos, the lowest close since December 28. The
nation’s largest company by market value said first-quarter net
income dropped 6 percent from a year earlier to 10.1 billion
pesos ($239 million) on higher expenses.  Rizal Commercial Banking Corp. (RCB)   rose 4.1 percent to
44.90 pesos, the biggest gain since Feb. 24. The bank sold 1.15
billion pesos of so-called certificate of deposits that will
mature in five-and-a-half years, documents on the sale show.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Norman P. Aquino in Manila at 
